solutions.content:
This question is a variation of 0/1 Unbounded Knapsack. Here we are allowed to pick coins any no. of times with 2 included constraints. 
- These picking up of coins from a particular pile cannot exceed k
- The coins in a particular pile are of different denomination

If these two constraints are removed the question is basic 0/1 Unbounded knapsack. So, similarly we have two options to go for.
- either to not pick any coin from a pile
- or pick 1 to k coins from a pile

Recursion
```
 public int maxValueOfCoins(List<List<Integer>> piles, int k) {
        int n=piles.size();
        return solve(piles,n,k);
    }

    public int solve(List<List<Integer>> piles,int i,int k){
        if(k==0)return 0;
        if(i==0)return 0;
        int best=solve(piles,i-1,k);
        List<Integer> pile=piles.get(i-1);
        int sum=0;
        for(int x=0;x<Math.min(k,pile.size());x++){
            sum+=pile.get(x);
            best=Math.max(best,+solve(piles,i-1,k-(x+1)));
        }
        return best;
    }
```
