# Intuition
We can iterate through piles and decide if we want to take something from the pile or not take it. 
If we decide to take coins from a particular pile, then we have the choice of how many coins to take.

# Approach
Let's try to think of a recursive solution. 
We have two choices, to take coins from a particular pile, or to take nothing. Suppose we start from the last pile, then we have two choices:

**notTake: f(i-1, k)**  // *just move to the next pile*
**take: (sum of x coins) + f(i-1, k-x)**  // *if we decide to take x coins from pile[i], then we need the sum of all coins from 0 to x, and my k is reduced accordingly, this can be done using a for loop*

Instead of calculating sum of x coins everytime I decide to take coins from the pile, we can make a prefix sum array so we can access the sum by going the xth index in the ith pile, it piles[i][x];


# Code
**Recursion:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int f(int i, int k, vector<vector<int>>& prefixPiles){
        // if we reach the end of piles, or k becomes 0 we return 0
        if(i<0 || k==0) return 0;

        int temp=prefixPiles[i].size();
        //we can only take coins from a pile n times.
        int n=min(temp, k);

        //move to the next index and k remains same
        int notTake=f(i-1, k, prefixPiles);

        int take=0;
        for(int j=0; j<n; j++){
            //take coins from pile
            take=max(take, prefixPiles[i][j]+f(i-1, k-j-1, prefixPiles));
        }
        //return max
        return max(take, notTake);
    }
    int maxValueOfCoins(vector<vector<int>>& piles, int k) {
        //making a prefix sum array to aviod adding coins everytime.
        vector<vector<int>> prefixPiles;
        for(int i=0; i<piles.size(); i++){
            vector<int> temp;
            temp.push_back(piles[i][0]);
            for(int j=1; j<piles[i].size(); j++){
                temp.push_back(temp[j-1]+piles[i][j]);
            }
            prefixPiles.push_back(temp);
        }
        //calling recursion starting from the last pile
        return f(piles.size()-1, k, prefixPiles);
    }
};
```

**Memoization:**
