# Intuition
we have to take k element from top so we have two options at every element either to take or not. SO we can apply here pick or notPick concept of dp

In basic method if we take 3 varibles i,j,k where i and j is for piles[i][j] then we have to apply 3-D dp which leads to TLE. 

To optimise this we can run a loop in j and take only those elements where k>0. it will reduce a lot of operations.

# Approach
For TLE CODE:
```
map<vector<int>,int>mp;
    int f(int i, int j, int k, vector<vector<int>> &piles){
        if(i>=piles.size() || j>=piles[i].size() || k<=0) return 0;

        if(mp.find({i,j,k})!=mp.end()){
            return mp[{i,j,k}];
        }

        int f1=piles[i][j]+f(i,j+1,k-1,piles);
        int f2=piles[i][j]+f(i+1,0,k-1,piles);
        int f3=f(i+1,0,k,piles);

        return mp[{i,j,k}]=max({f1,f2,f3});
    }
```

OPTIMISE APPROACH:
```
int f(int i,int k,vector<vector<int>> &v,vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        if(i>=n || k<=0) return 0;

        if(dp[i][k]!=-1) return dp[i][k];

        int notTake=f(i+1,k,v,dp);
        int Take=0;
        for(int j=0;j<v[i].size();++j){
            Take+=v[i][j];
            if(k-j-1>=0){
                notTake=max(notTake,Take+f(i+1,k-j-1,v,dp));
            }
        }

        return dp[i][k]=notTake;
    }
```

