solutions.content:
# Intuition
For each pile i, what will be the total value of coins we can collect if we choose the first j coins? Gives Hint for PrefixSum.
Than problem is reduced to Coin Change II Dp pattern.

# Approach
First take PrefixSum of all piles in same pile from top to bottom
such that pile[i][j] defines first j coins in ith pile.

Second Define State of DP:
DP[k][n]=optimal sum of k coins from first n piles

Third form a recurrance relation(same way as in coin change II):
set mAx = 0
if(we include nth pile) then
    loop: take max of all by considering first k coins of nth pile 
then if take max without including nth pile

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
PrefixSum = O(n*k)
DP with Memoization = O(n*k)*O(k) i.e. (No. of Call * work in each Calls) but overall will be only O(n*k) as very rarely in each call it will take O(k).

total TC = O(n*k) + O(n*k) = O(n*k)

- Space complexity:
For memoization matrix: O(n*k);

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int getMax(vector<vector<int>> &memo,vector<vector<int>> &pil,int k,int n){
        if(memo[k][n]==-1){
            if(k==0 || n==0) return 0;
            for(int i=0;i<pil[n-1].size();i++){
                if(i<k){
                    memo[k][n]=max(memo[k][n],pil[n-1][i]+getMax(memo,pil,k-(i+1),n-1));
                }
                else break;
            }
            memo[k][n]=max(memo[k][n],getMax(memo,pil,k,n-1));  
        }
        return memo[k][n];
    }

    int maxValueOfCoins(vector<vector<int>>& pil, int k) {
        for(int i=0;i<pil.size();i++){
            for(int j=1;j<pil[i].size();j++){
                pil[i][j]+=pil[i][j-1];
            }
        }
        vector<vector<int>> memo(k+1,vector<int>(pil.size()+1,-1));
        return getMax(memo,pil,k,pil.size());
    }
};
```

