solutions.content:
Either pick all k from previous piles, or choose j from current pile and pick k-j from previous piles
Recurrence relation:
f(i,k) represents the max sum of coins collected from first i piles and choosing k top coins.
```
f(i,k) = min(
			f(i-1,k) // pick k from previous piles
			,min(f(i-1,k-j-1)+sum(0 to j) for j = 0 to min(k,p[i-1].size())) // pick j+1 from current pile and k-j-1 from previous piles
		)
```

if k = 0, i.e. you can't pick any coin then ans = 0
if n = 0, i.e. you don't have any piles then ans = 0
Base cases :
f(0,k) = 0
f(n,0) = 0

Complexity at max will be O(n*k+2000). Why? beacuse its given that sum of all lengths of piles is at max 2000  
(1 <= k <= sum(piles[i].length) <= 2000). So you iterate over all **a[i][j]** at max once.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxValueOfCoins(vector<vector<int>>& a, int k) {
        int dp[1005][2005]={{0}};
        int n=a.size();
        //finding prefix sum before hand 
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<a[i].size();j++){
                a[i][j]+=a[i][j-1];
            }
        }
        //imagine a case when you have to choose from only one pile with diff value of k ,obviously it will be their prefix sum!!
       for(int j=1;j<2005;j++){
           if(j<=a[0].size())
           dp[0][j]+=a[0][j-1];
       }
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
           for(int j=1;j<2005;j++){
               int x=dp[i-1][j];  //if I dont choose any value from current i.e ith pile
               //now i will try to find max value if i choose 1,2,3...(min(a[i].size(),k)) ele fro current pile
               int y=0;
               for(int l=0;l<a[i].size();l++){
                   if(j-l-1>=0)  //(min(a[i].size(),k) condition.
                   y=max(y,a[i][l]+dp[i-1][j-l-1]);
               }
               dp[i][j]=max(x,y); //max of both

        }
        }

        return dp[n-1][k];

    }
};
```

